article.headline: W. Kentucky 83, Alabama A&amp,M 60
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. -- A.J. Slaughter scored 24 points and Western Kentucky defeated Alabama A&M 83-60 on Sunday. Slaughter, who was 8-for-10 shooting, led the Hilltoppers (7-3) to a 51.9 percent shooting performance (28 of 54). Western Kentucky hit 10 of 22 3-point shots compared to 4 of 16 by the Bulldogs (2-5). Jeremy Evans added 14 points and Sergio Kerusch had 10 points and 10 rebounds off the bench for Western Kentucky. The Hilltoppers outrebounded Alabama A&M 40-27, including six by D.J. Magley and five each from Mike Walker and Orlando Mandez-Valdez. Casey Cantley led the Bulldogs with 16 points and John Smith added 14 points and nine rebounds.
